'''Agni dhatu samadhi''' (火光三昧), is the [[spontaneous combustion]] of many [[Indian people|Indian]] [[Patriarch]]s of [[Chán Buddhism]],<ref>[http://www.hkbuddhist.org/magazine/493/493_10.html 虹化與火光三味]</ref> [[Chinese people|Chinese]] [[monk]]s Yuanmo (元模)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://w3.cbeta.org/result/normal/X84/1583_041.htm |title=《續燈正統》卷41 |access-date=2010-03-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090619202423/http://w3.cbeta.org/result/normal/X84/1583_041.htm |archive-date=2009-06-19 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> and Juxing.(具行) <ref>[http://www.bfnn.org/book/books/0096.htm 具行大師修行略傳]</ref> This is also the final earthly fate of the Hindu god [[Krishna]] in the [[Srimad Bhagavatam]].

