In [[demonology]], '''Bathin''' is a duke (Great Duke according to [[Pseudomonarchia Daemonum]]) of [[Hell]], who has under his command thirty legions of [[demon]]s. He knows the virtues of precious stones and [[herb]]s, and can bring men suddenly from one country to another. He helps one attain astral projection, and takes one wherever one wants to go.

He is depicted as a strong man with the tail of a [[Serpent (symbolism)|serpent]], riding a pale [[horse]].

He is mentioned in ''[[The Lesser Key of Solomon]]''.

''Other spellings'': Bathym, Mathim, Marthim.

