{{About|the album|the volume of poetry by [[Isaac Watts]]|Divine Songs Attempted in Easy Language for the Use of Children}}
'''''Divine Songs''''' is an album by [[Swamini Turiyasangitananda]], formerly known as [[Alice Coltrane]]. It is an album composed of devotional songs from the [[Hindu]] religion. The songs are accompanied by Turiya's signature playing on the [[Wurlitzer]] organ. She plays the songs on the organ, beginning with the traditional [[music of India|Indian]] mode but then improvises and stretches it until it turns back on itself musically. Her use of breaks, syncopation and harmonic invention re-image the songs into something original and nearly unclassifiable.
