{{Wiktionary|قلب}}
In [[Islamic philosophy]], the '''qalb''' ({{lang-ar|قلب}}), or [[heart]], is the origin of intentional activities, the cause behind all of humans intuitive deeds. While the brain handles the physical impressions, ''qalb'' (the heart) is responsible for apprehending.<ref>{{cite book |first=Alexander |last=Treiger |title=Inspired Knowledge in Islamic Thought: Al-Ghazali's Theory of Mystical Cognition and Its Avicennian Foundation |publisher=Routledge |year=2011 |isbn=978-1-136-65562-3 |page=8}}</ref> Heart and brain work together, but it is the heart where true knowledge can be received.
In Islamic thought, the heart is not the seat of feelings and emotions,<ref>{{cite book |first=Gustave E. |last=von Grunebaum |title=Medieval Islam: A Study in Cultural Orientation |publisher=University of Chicago Press |year=2010 |isbn=978-0-226-86492-1 |page=116}}</ref> but of ''[[rūḥ]]'' ({{lang-ar|روح|links=no}}): the immortal [[cognition]], the [[rational soul]].<ref>{{cite book |first=G. Hussein |last=Rassool |title=Islamic Counselling: An Introduction to Theory and Practice |publisher=Routledge |year=2015 |isbn=978-1-317-44125-0 |page=41}}</ref>
In the [[Quran]], the word ''qalb'' is used more than 130 times.{{citation needed|date=July 2017}}
==Stages of taming qalb== {{Unreferenced section|date=December 2009}} Qalb also refers to the second among the six purities or [[Lataif-e-sitta]] in Sufi philosophy. To attend [[Tasfiya-e-Qalb]], the [[Salik]] needs to achieve the following sixteen goals. #[[Zuhd]] or abstention from evil #[[Taqwa]] or God consciousness #[[War'a]] or attempt to get away from things that are not related to Allah. #[[Tawakkul]] or being content with whatever Allah gives #[[Sabr (Islamic term)|Sabır]] or patience regarding whatever [[Allah]] fe Subhan ta'âlâ does #[[Shukr]] or gratefulness for whatever Allah gives #Raza or seeking happiness of Allah #[[Khauf]] or fear of Allah's wrath #[[Rija]] or hope of Allah's blessing #[[Yaqeen]] or complete faith in Allah #[[Ikhlas]] or purity of intention #[[Sidq]] or bearing truth of Allah #[[Muraqabah]] or total focus on Allah #[[Khulq]] or humbleness for Allah #[[Dhikr]] or remembrance of Allah #[[Khuloot]] or isolation from everyone except Allah
