{{Jainism}}
'''Samudravijaya''' was the father of Lord [[Neminatha]] (twenty-second [[Tirthankara]]) and brother of [[Vasudeva]] (father of [[Krishna]]).{{sfn|Shah|2004|p=24}} He was born to King Andhakavrishni of Harivamsa (dynasty) in [[Sauripura (Dvaraka)]] where he later ruled as a king.{{sfn|Jain|2009|p=88}} He married princess Shivadevi.{{sfn|von Glasenapp|1999|p=317}}

== Literature ==
The [[Harivamsa Purana]] of Acharya [[Jinasena]] throws some light on the life of Samudravijaya.{{cn|date=June 2016}}

